result: Larry Page is an American computer scientist and entrepreneur best known as one of the co-founders of Google, along with Sergey Brin. He served as the CEO of Google's parent company, Alphabet Inc., until December 2019. Born on March 26, 1973, in East Lansing, Michigan, Larry Page played a significant role in the development of Google's search engine, which revolutionized the way information is accessed on the internet. Alongside his contributions to search technology, he is also recognized for his interest in advancing and investing in other technological innovations and ideas.
